  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (MRL 3, W-EP-04 trigger)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. Model Risk Level is set to 3 for this package. Twelve of thirteen credibility factors have been assessed; the factor 'Equivalency of input parameters' carries factorStatus 'not-assessed' on the grounds that the modelling team considered it inapplicable because boundary conditions were derived directly from bench measurements — however, the correct ASME V&V 40 encoding for a factor judged inapplicable is 'not-applicable', not 'not-assessed'. The mismatch means the factor is formally unassessed at MRL 3, constituting an epistemic gap that materially weakens package credibility (W-EP-04).",
  "assuranceLevel": "Low",
  "couName": "VAD use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class III",
  "modelRiskLevel": 3,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl3",
